         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">12/1/87. ¶  ¶ Let me thank you for your most kind letter, dear Mr Ridley; and let me express my grateful recognition also particularly, for the gracious manner, in which you alluded to me in your impo...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">87.01.12d</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Henry Ridley</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RBG Kew, Kew correspondence, Australia, Mueller, unbound letters 1881-96.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">12/1/87.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Let me thank you for your most kind letter, dear Mr Ridley; and let me express my grateful recognition also particularly, for the gracious manner, in which you alluded to me in your important treatise on new Papuan Orchids.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Ridley (1886), p. 321:</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; margin-left: 0.5in; text-indent: 0in; "
                        xml:lang="en">The greater portion of the flowering plants are being described by Baron von Mueller, who is probably better acquainted with the flora of this island than anyone else in the empire.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M repeated his thanks in M to H. Ridley, 21 February 1887.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have not heard from Mr Forbes for a considerable time, but learned from the daily journals, that he was ill with fever and thought of leaving for Europe:<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>When Henry Forbes run out of funds for exploration in May 1886, instead of returning to England<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>as planned<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>he had accepted a position as Government Island at Dinner Island (now Samari Island). He was reported as ill with fever in November 1886 (e.g.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Daily telegraph<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        </seg>(Sydney), 18 November 1886, p. 5), but as recovered in December (e.g.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Sydney morning herald</seg>, 1 December 1886, p. 4),<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>and was expected to remain at Dinner Island until March 1887 (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Brisbane courier</seg>, 25 December 1886, p. 5.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>no doubt your Department will have direct communication from him.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very considerate of you, that you informed the recipients of sets of Mr Forbes’s plants that arrangements had been made for the elaboration of most of the Dicotyledoneae here. My progress with them has been slow; but [as] I shall soon have cleared off the heavy departmental, which arose in 1886, I see good prospects for finishing the Dicotyledoneae (with the exception of the already exempted orders) in 1887. Should however my health break down or any other hindrances intervene, then your honored Chief, Mr Carruthers, will be so informed; so that Mr Forbes's interests do not suffer.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Will send you any dried specimens of Papuan orchids, which can be spared.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn2" n="3">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Written in the left margin on the back of the folio.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>By the Lusitania through a Melbourne (Tate’s) Agency went 635 spec of dried plants to your [est.] from here on the 24 Dec 1886.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn3" n="4">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3347in; text-indent: -0.3347in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>i.e. to the British Museum (Natural History). Written in the central and left margins on the front of the folio.</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plantnames"
               style="font-style: italic; font-size: 10pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Dicotyledoneae</p>
         </div>
